  "text": "HTTP filter factory registration and instantiation in Envoy (v1.31.2) follows a multi-stage process:\n\n**1. Factory Interface Definition:**\nThe `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` interface (envoy/server/filter_config.h:273) is the base class that all HTTP filter factories must implement. It extends `HttpFilterConfigFactoryBase` (line 203) and declares the pure virtual method `createFilterFactoryFromProto()` that returns an `absl::StatusOr<Http::FilterFactoryCb>`.\n\n**2. Factory Registry:**\nThe `FactoryRegistry` template class (envoy/registry/registry.h:166) manages a static global registry of all factories indexed by name. Factories are registered at startup using the `RegisterFactory<T, Base>` template (envoy/registry/registry.h:507), which is instantiated through `REGISTER_FACTORY` or `LEGACY_REGISTER_FACTORY` macros. The registry stores pointers to factory instances in a static `absl::flat_hash_map<std::string, Base*>` (line 191).\n\n**3. Filter Chain Factory Interface:**\nThe `FilterChainFactory` interface (envoy/http/filter_factory.h:89) defines the `createFilterChain()` method, which is called when a new HTTP stream is created. It takes a `FilterChainManager` sink to receive filter instances.\n\n**4. HTTP Connection Manager Configuration:**\nThe `HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory` (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h:53) is a network filter factory that creates HTTP connections. Its implementation (config.cc:274) calls the `HttpConnectionManagerConfig` constructor, which processes the list of configured HTTP filters and creates `FilterFactoryCb` callbacks during initialization.\n\n**5. Filter Chain Creation:**\nThe `HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain()` (config.h:141, config.cc:780) implements the `FilterChainFactory` interface. It calls `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()` (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.cc:17) with a pre-built list of filter factories.\n\nThe filter chain creation happens during server startup: each configured filter is looked up in the registry, its `createFilterFactoryFromProto()` method is called to produce a `FilterFactoryCb` (a std::function<void(FilterChainFactoryCallbacks&)>), and this callback is stored in a `FilterFactoriesList` (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h:51).\n\n**6. Per-Request Filter Instantiation:**\nWhen a new HTTP request arrives, the filter chain creation is triggered per-request/per-stream:\n\n- The `FilterChainFactory::createFilterChain()` is called by the stream manager\n- `FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()` iterates through stored `FilterFactoryCb` callbacks\n- For each callback, `FilterChainManager::applyFilterFactoryCb()` is called (source/common/http/filter_manager.h:697)\n- The implementation in FilterManager (source/common/http/filter_manager.cc:551) creates a `FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl` and executes the stored callback with it\n- The callback (created by the filter factory) calls `addStreamDecoderFilter()` or `addStreamEncoderFilter()` on the callbacks object (source/common/http/filter_manager.h:918, 924)\n- These methods instantiate the actual filter instance and wrap it in `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter` or `ActiveStreamEncoderFilter`, adding it to the stream's filter lists\n\n**7. Example Implementation:**\nThe router filter (source/extensions/filters/http/router/config.h:18) shows the complete pattern: `RouterFilterConfig` extends `FactoryBase<ConfigProto>` and implements `createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped()` (config.cc:14) which returns a lambda that captures the filter configuration and calls `callbacks.addStreamDecoderFilter()` with a new `Router::ProdFilter` instance. The factory is registered with `LEGACY_REGISTER_FACTORY()` (config.cc:32).\n\n**Key Design Points:**\n- Configuration-time: Factories are looked up by name in the registry, and FilterFactoryCb callbacks are created and stored\n- Request-time: Stored callbacks are executed to create actual filter instances for each request/stream\n- The FilterFactoryCb std::function separates configuration (factories) from instantiation (callbacks), allowing efficient per-request filter creation\n- Common factory base class (source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h:63) provides template boilerplate for implementing filter factories"
